1) The pre- and post-processing data produced by VASPKIT may be used in any publications provided that its use is explicitly acknowledged. A suitable reference for VASPKIT is:
   [1] V. Wang, N. Xu, J.-C. LIU, G. Tang, W.-T. Geng, VASPKIT: A User-Friendly Interface Facilitating High-Throughput Computing and Analysis Using VASP Code, Computer Physics Communications, 267, 108033 (2021).

2) Please cite the following work if you used the module 'Thermal corrections for Gas' and the module 'Symmerty Finding for Molecules and Clusters':
   [1] Pilati, T. and A. Forni, SYMMOL: a program to find the maximum symmetry group in an atom cluster, given a prefixed tolerance, Journal of Applied Crystallography 31, 503-504 (1998).

3) Please cite the following work if you used the module 'K-Path utility':
   [1] A. Togo and I. Tanaka, Spglib: a software library for crystal symmetry search, arXiv:1808.015900.
   [2] Y. Hinuma, G. Pizzi, Y. Kumagai, F. Oba, I. Tanaka, Band structure diagram paths based on crystallography, Computational Materials Science 128, 140 (2017).
   [3] V. Wang, G. Tang, Y.-C. Liu, R.-T. Wang, H. Mizuseki, Y. Kawazeo, J. Nara, W.-T. Geng, High-Throughput Computational Screening of Two-Dimensional Semiconductors, Journal of Physical Chemistry Letters 13, 11581 (2022). 

